In the realm of pandas skills, you likely focused on selecting specific columns (using DF.columns),

Today's summary of learning
To check the columns of a DataFrame, you can use DF.columns, and you can select specific rows
using iloc based on integer positions. Additionally, you can select multiple rows and columns using
slicing, where the last value is inclusive when used with loc.
Through mastering these skills, you gain the flexibility to manipulate columns and rows within a
DataFrame effectively.

What is Titanic dataset?
On April 15, 1912, the Titanic sank after colliding
with an iceberg during its maiden voyage.
Unfortunately, due to insufficient lifeboats, 1,502
out of 2,224 passengers and crew perished.
While survival was somewhat related to luck, it
seems that certain groups of people had a higher
chance of survival than others.
Through the data, we can analyze "What types of
people were more likely to survive?"
What is Titanic dataset?
You can use Seaborn's "load_dataset" to retrieve the Titanic dataset.
Titanic dataset Column Descriptions
survived Survival status (1: Survived, 0: Died)
pclass Passenger class (1st class, 2nd class, 3rd class)
sex Gender
age Age
sibsp Number of siblings/spouses aboard
parch Number of parents/children aboard
fare Fare
embarked Port of embarkation (S, C, Q)
class Same as pclass
who Who (man, woman, child)
adult_male Adult male status
deck Deck number (mix of alphabets and numbers)
embark_town Name of embarkation town
alive Survival status (yes, no)
alone Alone aboard status
Family Travel
